import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="site", y="yield", data=data, ci=None)
    ax.axhline(y=data['yield'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean Yield')
    ax.set(xlabel='Site', ylabel='Yield')
    ax.set_title('What is the average yield per site?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x="variety", y="yield", data=data, ax=ax)
    ax.set_xlabel("Variety")
    ax.set_ylabel("Yield")
    ax.set_title("How does the yield vary by variety?")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='yield', data=data, ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of yield over the years?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Yield')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='yield', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['yield'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['yield'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['yield'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['yield'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of yield across all sites?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_pivot = data.pivot_table(index='variety', columns='site', values='yield')
    sns.heatmap(data_pivot, annot=True, fmt=".2f", cmap='YlGnBu')
    plt.title('How does the yield vary by site and variety?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
